What does this do: private String[] dessert = new String[3];
Creates three different strings for the item "dessert"
What does this do: private String[] postres = {"rice pudding", "pan dulce", "bunuelos"}
Gives the three dessert items
How are they different?
One gives three random strings the other gives already called strings
